description:
reference to a document depicting the power loss of a component with losses not proportional to I² during the state under load up to the maximum possible continuous rms current (=  rated current) and measured at rated ambient temperature and at rated frequency.
1 The power loss includes the losses of all current carrying paths of the component.
2 The power loss curve in dependency of the variable load current can normally not be expressed by a formula and shall be depicted by a curve including all relevant service conditions, for example ambient temperature, frequency, under which the curve has been obtained.
3 Power loss curves  at different service conditions can be obtained by modifying their values.
4 Such curves ocurr for example in unbalanced states of an object.
